cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.NA, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper deals with distributed computing systems and proposes a solution to the straggler mitigation problem in distributed matrix multiplication. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes polynomial coding schemes for distributed matrix multiplication and discusses the decoding problem. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with heterogeneous computing systems and proposes a solution to the straggler problem. 
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper discusses the numerical results of the proposed bivariate polynomial coding scheme. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new coding scheme for distributed matrix multiplication, which can be seen as an algorithmic contribution.
